Preface

This is a book about ocean waves, their evolution and their interaction with the environment. It presents a summary and uniÔ¨Ācation of my knowledge of wave growth, nonlinear interactions and dissipation of surface gravity waves, and this knowledge is applied to the problem of the two-way interaction of wind and waves, with consequences for atmosphere and ocean circulation.
