Starting from the Lagrangian of linear deep water waves we have obtained the appropriate evolution equations for wave groups in slowly varying circumstances caused by slowly varying currents or water depth. There are, however, other causes for evolution of wave groups. Waves may grow because of the action of wind and they may loose energy because of dissipation due to e.g. white capping. Furthermore, Ô¨Ānite amplitude ocean waves are subject

